ysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/WickAlgebra/Basic.html#FieldSpecification.WickAlgebra.ofFieldOp\">FieldSpecification.WickAlgebra.ofFieldOp</a> <span class=\"fn\">φs</span><a href=\"./Init/GetElem.html#GetElem.getElem\">[</a><span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">j</span></span><a href=\"./Init/GetElem.html#GetElem.getElem\">]</a>)</span></span>,\n        <span class=\"fn\">⋯</span><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Subtype.mk\">⟩</a>\n    <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#ite\">else</a>       <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Subtype.mk\">⟨</a><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/WickAlgebra/SuperCommute.html#FieldSpecification.WickAlgebra.superCommute\">FieldSpecification.WickAlgebra.superCommute</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/WickAlgebra/Basic.html#FieldSpecification.WickAlgebra.anPart\">FieldSpecification.WickAlgebra.anPart</a> <span class=\"fn\">φs</span><a href=\"./Init/GetElem.html#GetElem.getElem\">[</a><span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">j</span></span><a href=\"./Init/GetElem.html#GetElem.getElem\">]</a>)</span>)</span>\n          <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/WickAlgebra/Basic.html#FieldSpecification.WickAlgebra.ofFieldOp\">FieldSpecification.WickAlgebra.ofFieldOp</a> <span class=\"fn\">φ</span>)</span></span>,\n        <span class=\"fn\">⋯</span><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Subtype.mk\">⟩</a>) <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HMul.hMul\">*</a>     <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">φsΛ</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/WickContraction/StaticContract.html#WickContraction.staticContract\">staticContract</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"For a list `φs = φ₀…φₙ` of `𝓕.FieldOp`, a Wick contraction `φsΛ` of `φs`, an element `φ` of\n`𝓕.FieldOp`, a `i ≤ φs.length` and a `k` in `φsΛ.uncontracted`, then\n`(φsΛ ↩Λ φ i (some k)).staticContract` is equal to the product of\n- `[anPart φ, φs[k]]ₛ` if `i ≤ k` or `[anPart φs[k], φ]ₛ` if `k < i`\n- `φsΛ.staticContract`.\n\nThe proof of this result ultimately is a consequence of definitions.\n","docLink":"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/WickContraction/StaticContract.html#WickContraction.staticContract_insert_some","kind":"theorem","line":49,"name":"WickContraction.staticContract_insert_some","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L49-L75"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/WickContraction/StaticContract.html#WickContraction.staticContract_insert_none\"><span class=\"name\">WickContraction</span>.<span class=\"name\">staticContract_insert_none</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span> : <a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification\">FieldSpecification</a>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">φ</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification.FieldOp\">FieldOp</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">φs</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification.FieldOp\">FieldOp</a></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">φsΛ</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/WickContraction/Basic.html#WickContraction\">WickContraction</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">φs</span>.<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List.length\">length</a></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">i</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Fin\">Fin</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">φs</span>.<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List.length\">length</a></span>.<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat.succ\">succ</a></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/WickContraction/InsertAndContract.html#WickContraction.insertAndContract\">insertAndContract</a> <span class=\"fn\">φ</span> <span class=\"fn\">φsΛ</span> <span class=\"fn\">i</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Option.none\">none</a>)</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/WickContraction/StaticContract.html#WickContraction.staticContract\">staticContract</a></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">φsΛ</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/WickContraction/StaticContract.html#WickContraction.staticContract\">staticContract</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"For a list `φs = φ₀…φₙ` of `𝓕.FieldOp`, a Wick contraction `φsΛ` of `φs`, an element `φ` of\n`𝓕.FieldOp`, and a `i ≤ φs.length`, then the following relation holds:\n\n`(φsΛ ↩Λ φ i none).staticContract = φsΛ.staticContract`\n\nThe proof of this result ultimately is a consequence of definitions.\n","docLink":"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/WickContraction/StaticContract.html#WickContraction.staticContract_insert_none","kind":"theorem","line":33,"name":"WickContraction.staticContract_insert_none","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L33-L47"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">noncomputable def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/WickContraction/StaticContract.html#WickContraction.staticContract\"><span class=\"name\">WickContraction</span>.<span class=\"name\">staticContract</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span> : <a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification\">FieldSpecification</a>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">φs</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification.FieldOp\">FieldOp</a></span></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">φsΛ</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/WickContraction/Basic.html#WickContraction\">WickContraction</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">φs</span>.<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List.length\">length</a></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\">↥<span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Algebra/Subalgebra/Basic.html#Subalgebra.center\">Subalgebra.center</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Complex/Basic.html#Complex\">ℂ</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/WickAlgebra/Basic.html#FieldSpecification.WickAlgebra\">WickAlgebra</a></span>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"For a list `φs` of `𝓕.FieldOp` and a Wick contraction `φsΛ`, the\nelement of the center of `𝓕.WickAlgebra`, `φsΛ.staticContract` is defined as the product\nof `[anPart φs[j], φs[k]]ₛ` over contracted pairs `{j, k}` in `φsΛ`\nwith `j < k`. ","docLink":"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/WickContraction/StaticContract.html#WickContraction.staticContract","kind":"def","line":22,"name":"WickContraction.staticContract","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L22-L31"}}],"imports":["Init","PhysLean.QFT.PerturbationTheory.WickContraction.InsertAndContract","PhysLean.QFT.PerturbationTheory.WickAlgebra.NormalOrder.Lemmas"],"instances":[],"name":"PhysLean.QFT.PerturbationTheory.WickContraction.StaticContract"}